window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Hamelin, a village separated from the rest of the world, has a deadly problem.</b> Fierce, flying beasts ravage and cull the sparse human population, forcing Hamelins citizens to live within the safety of her boundaries. With no help in sight, the village leaders look to their god, the Provider, for salvation, and they unearth <b>a chilling answer to their problem.</b> The Tournament of the Kindredâ€”a much-celebrated, barbaric event that pits four gladiators against each other in deadly combat. </p> <p>Winning the Tournament brings rich rewards, fame, and glory to ones bloodline. Losing, however, results in a lethal trip to the Sacrificial Altar for you and all those who share your blood: man, woman, and child. The sacrifice is said to be a blood offering to the Provider for reprievea necessary evil for the greater good of all. Neven Oakfall, adolescent town historian and librarian, is chosen by random draw to fight for the survival of his bloodline. </p> <p>After a life behind a desk, Neven must find the courage deep within himself to defeat his stronger opponents, for he discovers that <b>much more than the lives of those he loves hangs in the balance.</b> An evil lurks, waiting for its moment to deliver the death blow to the village, and Neven is all that stands in its way, whether he likes it or not.</p>"; 
